00:10:20,166 --> 00:10:21,541
Seriously?

250
00:10:21,625 --> 00:10:22,750
Well, at least he's having fun.

251
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:25,458
[groaning]

252
00:10:26,833 --> 00:10:28,875
Whoa.
Where the heck am I?

253
00:10:28,958 --> 00:10:30,708
-[knocking on door]
-Who is it?

254
00:10:30,791 --> 00:10:32,875
[NURSE]
Time for a new stick 'n drip!

255
00:10:32,958 --> 00:10:35,083
I'm here to change your IV.

256
00:10:35,166 --> 00:10:37,000
Hah! It's you!

257
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:39,875
Back when I was hospitalized
after falling down the stairs

258
00:10:39,958 --> 00:10:41,291
at the nata de coco plant,

259
00:10:41,375 --> 00:10:42,833
you were my hot nurse!

260
00:10:42,916 --> 00:10:43,875
[giggles]

261
00:10:43,958 --> 00:10:45,625
Been a minute, hasn't it?

262
00:10:50,500 --> 00:10:51,833
[ALLO]
It was a cold day.

263
00:10:51,916 --> 00:10:53,708
Freezing rain was falling,

264
00:10:53,791 --> 00:10:55,916
like angry tears from the sky.

265
00:11:22,916 --> 00:11:25,375
[footsteps approaching]

266
00:11:25,458 --> 00:11:26,750
Huh?

267
00:11:36,875 --> 00:11:38,250
Be a better man.

268
00:11:38,333 --> 00:11:39,708
You can start
by taking more pride

269
00:11:39,791 --> 00:11:40,666
in your appearance.

270
00:11:44,166 --> 00:11:47,583
♪

271
00:11:56,916 --> 00:11:58,083
[YANG]
Come with me.

272
00:11:58,166 --> 00:11:59,708
I'll buy you something to eat.

273
00:12:01,791 --> 00:12:04,375
[ALLO grunts, panting]

274
00:12:04,458 --> 00:12:09,333
♪

275
00:12:11,333 --> 00:12:12,666
[GRAS]
It was a summer day.

276
00:12:12,750 --> 00:12:15,541
The sun shone warmly,
like the mysterious spot

277
00:12:15,625 --> 00:12:17,833
in a swimming pool
full of happy children.

278
00:12:17,916 --> 00:12:21,833
[hair bouncing]

279
00:12:21,916 --> 00:12:23,791
[ALLO humming]

280
00:12:29,791 --> 00:12:32,166
[humming continues]

281
00:12:35,541 --> 00:12:39,708
[music playing over headphones]

282
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:45,125
[GRAS] Hmm?

283
00:12:48,666 --> 00:12:51,708
[bouncing continues]

284
00:12:58,458 --> 00:13:00,166
You can be a better man.

285
00:13:00,250 --> 00:13:02,541
First start by taking more pride
in your appearance.

286
00:13:06,541 --> 00:13:07,416
Huh?

287
00:13:08,500 --> 00:13:09,916
[ALLO grunts]

288
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:11,458
I said you can be a better man

289
00:13:11,541 --> 00:13:12,875
by taking care
of your appearance.

290
00:13:12,958 --> 00:13:14,375
What?

291
00:13:14,458 --> 00:13:15,500
Say it again?

292
00:13:15,583 --> 00:13:17,583
I'm trying
to help you be better!

293
00:13:17,666 --> 00:13:21,166
So all you have to do is put
some effort into how you look!

294
00:13:21,250 --> 00:13:23,958
Huh? You're gonna have
to say it one more time.

295
00:13:24,041 --> 00:13:26,833
You look like barn feed!

296
00:13:26,916 --> 00:13:28,208
Fix it!

297
00:13:28,291 --> 00:13:29,583
I'm trying to
change your life,

298
00:13:29,666 --> 00:13:31,416
and you're making it
so hard!

299
00:13:31,500 --> 00:13:33,041
It just looks like
you're chewing the air.

300
00:13:33,125 --> 00:13:34,291
I still can't hear you.

301
00:13:34,375 --> 00:13:35,916
Forget it! Moving on!

302
00:13:38,458 --> 00:13:40,958
Come with me.
I'll buy you something to eat.

303
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:44,458
You wanna look like
a psychedelic earthworm

304
00:13:44,541 --> 00:13:46,000
making friends
with a cardboard box,

305
00:13:46,083 --> 00:13:47,583
-why should it matter to me?
-[GRAS panting]

306
00:13:47,666 --> 00:13:50,458
Try to pay it forward-- Ow!

307
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:55,666
[giggles]
Been a minute, hasn't it?

308
00:13:55,750 --> 00:13:57,791
What the hell
are you doing here?

309
00:13:57,875 --> 00:13:59,416
And why did you put me
through that nightmare?

310
00:13:59,500 --> 00:14:02,333
I was chased and almost killed
by rabid thugs!

311
00:14:02,416 --> 00:14:04,166
I'm sorry about that.

312
00:14:04,250 --> 00:14:07,166
He was upset because his wife
found out about me that day.

313
00:14:07,250 --> 00:14:08,791
Earth was way too dramatic.

314
00:14:08,875 --> 00:14:10,291
So I moved back to Odwarla.

315
00:14:10,375 --> 00:14:12,666
Yeah. I don't blame you.

316
00:14:12,750 --> 00:14:14,958
But here we are again,
so I guess it didn't work

317
00:14:15,041 --> 00:14:17,041
-as well as I had hoped.
-[ROBBY chuckles]

318
00:14:17,125 --> 00:14:19,500
That means it must be destiny.

319
00:14:19,583 --> 00:14:20,875
♪

320
00:14:20,958 --> 00:14:22,750
[ROBBY gulps, giggles]

321
00:14:22,833 --> 00:14:24,375
♪

322
00:14:24,458 --> 00:14:25,458
[MERMAN sighs]

323
00:14:26,750 --> 00:14:28,916
Gyo-Gyo, you are
blowing my mind!

324
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:31,125
The webbing you have gets
the dishes that clean?

325
00:14:31,208 --> 00:14:33,791
How does it work?
Can I see them?

326
00:14:33,875 --> 00:14:35,791
What, my hands?
That's kinda awkward.

327
00:14:35,875 --> 00:14:38,541
[HATCHI] Oh! I'll bet you're
a really fast swimmer!

328
00:14:38,625 --> 00:14:40,458
Uh, sure.
I mean, they told you

329
00:14:40,541 --> 00:14:42,000
we all used to live
in the ocean, right?

330
00:14:42,083 --> 00:14:44,500
Yeah, and I've been wondering
how you breathe here.

331
00:14:44,583 --> 00:14:46,416
With lungs, just like you.

332
00:14:46,500 --> 00:14:48,250
But we can still use our gills
if we're underwater.

333
00:14:48,333 --> 00:14:49,708
That's so cool!

334
00:14:49,791 --> 00:14:51,750
So you can basically live
wherever you want then?

335
00:14:51,833 --> 00:14:54,208
Sort of. We've been living
on land for a while,

336
00:14:54,291 --> 00:14:55,791
so our gills are
way too weak to use

337
00:14:55,875 --> 00:14:57,333
for long stretches of time.

338
00:14:57,416 --> 00:14:58,875
That's why I'm saving up
all the money

339
00:14:58,958 --> 00:15:00,083
I make working here.

340
00:15:00,166 --> 00:15:02,208
I want to buy
a sweet underwater suit.

341
00:15:02,291 --> 00:15:05,166
Every mer-thing in captivity
longs to return to the sea.

342
00:15:05,250 --> 00:15:07,791
Man, what you talkin' about
"captivity." Land life's great.

343
00:15:07,875 --> 00:15:09,666
But I gotta eat, and nabbin'
that prize fish

344
00:15:09,750 --> 00:15:11,458
would help a lot.

345
00:15:11,541 --> 00:15:13,791
I must catch
the Odwarla oarfish!

346
00:15:13,875 --> 00:15:16,041
Wait, what do you mean
"prize fish?"

347
00:15:16,125 --> 00:15:18,208
Why are you hung up
on this oarfish?

348
00:15:18,291 --> 00:15:20,916
Because they say if you make
a fish loaf out of it

349
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:22,333
and feed it
to the Odwarlan god,

350
00:15:22,416 --> 00:15:24,291
it can drastically
change your life!

351
00:15:24,375 --> 00:15:26,875
I'm not sure how much,
but you get enough reward money

352
00:15:26,958 --> 00:15:28,041
to make it worth the hunt.

353
00:15:28,125 --> 00:15:29,541
Just tell me what I have to do.

354
00:15:29,625 --> 00:15:32,250
You'll need to buy
some special equipment.

355
00:15:32,333 --> 00:15:34,541
But it's the biggest jackpot
you'll ever see.

356
00:15:34,625 --> 00:15:37,625
I tell you what, I promised
my girl when I got one,

357
00:15:37,708 --> 00:15:39,500
I'd give her
a real wedding ceremony.

358
00:15:39,583 --> 00:15:41,500
We weren't able to have one
when we got married.

359
00:15:41,583 --> 00:15:44,083
♪

360
00:15:44,166 --> 00:15:46,750
[HATCHI]
An Odwarla oarfish, huh?

361
00:15:46,833 --> 00:15:48,875
Who knew?
But after hearing all that,

362
00:15:48,958 --> 00:15:50,500
I kinda want
to catch one myself.

363
00:15:50,583 --> 00:15:51,708
Me too.

364
00:15:51,791 --> 00:15:53,208
I wonder what mer-folk
give each other

365
00:15:53,291 --> 00:15:54,750
when they get engaged.

366
00:15:54,833 --> 00:15:55,958
They can't exactly wear rings

367
00:15:56,041 --> 00:15:57,333
with webbed fingers, can they?

368
00:15:57,416 --> 00:15:59,250
That's what you're thinking
about right now?

369
00:15:59,333 --> 00:16:01,416
[MANAGER]
Let's warm up that joy!

370
00:16:01,500 --> 00:16:04,125
-Thanks for dining with us!
-Thanks for dining with us!

371
00:16:04,208 --> 00:16:06,041
I heard that too much joy
gives you gas.

372
00:16:06,125 --> 00:16:08,291
[ROBBY] Hatchi! Ikku!
Over here!

373
00:16:08,375 --> 00:16:10,375
It's quittin' time, you guys!
Let's go!

374
00:16:10,458 --> 00:16:13,250
Go where, exactly?
And we're not even open yet!

375
00:16:13,333 --> 00:16:15,416
Wait a minute, aren't you
supposed to be in the hospital?

376
00:16:15,500 --> 00:16:17,041
That was then, Ikku.

377
00:16:17,125 --> 00:16:18,666
Catching the Oarfish is now.

378
00:16:18,750 --> 00:16:20,375
And check out
all our clutch new gear!

379
00:16:20,458 --> 00:16:22,000
You got fishing gear?

380
00:16:22,083 --> 00:16:24,416
Don't insult the brilliant
invention that rests beside me.

381
00:16:24,500 --> 00:16:25,875
This is more than
just fishing gear.

382
00:16:25,958 --> 00:16:28,083
It's the Premium
Oarfish Hunting Set!

383
00:16:28,166 --> 00:16:32,666
[fast forward talking]

384
00:16:32,750 --> 00:16:34,083
You dumbass!

385
00:16:34,166 --> 00:16:35,958
You let that hot nurse
snow you again?

386
00:16:36,041 --> 00:16:38,166
That sounds like so much fun!
Let's do it!

387
00:16:38,250 --> 00:16:39,458
-[IKKU] Huh?
-[ROBBY] Oh!

388
00:16:39,541 --> 00:16:41,541
There's a huge cash reward
if we catch one.

389
00:16:41,625 --> 00:16:43,791
Get out of my dreams right now!
You know about that?

390
00:16:43,875 --> 00:16:46,208
Dude, if we work together
on this, we'll score easily!

391
00:16:46,291 --> 00:16:47,916
As long as we score
with Gyo-Gyo.

392
00:16:48,000 --> 00:16:50,041
-Who?
-Uh...

393
00:16:51,083 --> 00:16:52,125
Hi?

394
00:16:52,208 --> 00:16:54,250
♪

395
00:16:54,333 --> 00:16:56,250
Come on,
why aren't they biting?

396
00:16:56,333 --> 00:16:57,958
This day and age,
we should be able to order

397
00:16:58,041 --> 00:16:59,750
these fish things
off the dark web!

398
00:16:59,833 --> 00:17:02,250
String on a stick, is this
the modern world or not?

399
00:17:02,333 --> 00:17:03,500
Even in the modern world,

400
00:17:03,583 --> 00:17:05,208
hot nurses can lead
to bad decisions.

401
00:17:05,291 --> 00:17:06,500
[ROBBY]
It's the premium set,

402
00:17:06,583 --> 00:17:08,291
and it's the best decision
I've ever made!

403
00:17:08,375 --> 00:17:11,250
[IKKU]
Ugh! A buffet of disease.

404
00:17:11,333 --> 00:17:13,708
You guys!
They're beautiful!

405
00:17:13,791 --> 00:17:16,416
Look at this colorful
treasure trove of fishies!

406
00:17:16,500 --> 00:17:18,791
None of these are
the Odwarla oarfish though.

407
00:17:18,875 --> 00:17:21,166
You just had to get
the premium set, didn't you?

408
00:17:21,250 --> 00:17:23,416
Damn it!
I'll do it another way.

409
00:17:25,500 --> 00:17:27,583
[ROBBY]
Hizakuriger!

410
00:17:27,666 --> 00:17:30,875
♪

411
00:17:54,500 --> 00:18:01,500
Hizakuriger!

412
00:18:04,041 --> 00:18:05,958
You've forced yourself
on me, now what?

413
00:18:06,041 --> 00:18:07,916
Now, we're gonna thrust
ourselves into the sea

414
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:09,250
and catch that damn fish!

415
00:18:09,333 --> 00:18:10,583
Let's go!

416
00:18:10,666 --> 00:18:12,583
[ROBBY yelling]

417
00:18:12,666 --> 00:18:16,000
[splashing]

418
00:18:16,083 --> 00:18:18,708
♪

419
00:18:19,791 --> 00:18:21,458
Hope they know something
that I don't,

420
00:18:21,541 --> 00:18:23,708
‘cause I don't think that thing
was designed for watersports.

421
00:18:23,791 --> 00:18:24,708
Eh?

422
00:18:24,791 --> 00:18:28,083
♪

423
00:18:35,333 --> 00:18:37,083
[ROBBY]
Here, fishy, fishy, fishy!

424
00:18:37,166 --> 00:18:38,208
Come to Robby!

425
00:18:38,291 --> 00:18:39,166
[metallic creaking]

426
00:18:39,250 --> 00:18:42,000
Wait, that sound.

427
00:18:42,083 --> 00:18:44,291
Hey, did you make sure
this thing won't leak?

428
00:18:44,375 --> 00:18:46,041
You love bringing down
the mood, don't you?

429
00:18:46,125 --> 00:18:48,166
It's built for space,
it can handle some moisture.

430
00:18:48,250 --> 00:18:50,000
Space has zero atmospheres,

431
00:18:50,083 --> 00:18:51,958
which isn't much different
from sea level.

432
00:18:52,041 --> 00:18:53,750
But for every ten meters
we go under,

433
00:18:53,833 --> 00:18:55,500
it adds more
atmospheric pressure.

434
00:18:55,583 --> 00:18:56,791
So a hundred meters under

435
00:18:56,875 --> 00:18:59,041
is like ten times
the pressure in space.

436
00:18:59,125 --> 00:19:00,791
[gurgling]
There. You see?

437
00:19:00,875 --> 00:19:02,416
What? You should've been
doing something

438
00:19:02,500 --> 00:19:03,791
instead of Hatchi-splaining!

439
00:19:03,875 --> 00:19:04,916
Priorities! Yah!

440
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:06,291
Get to the highest point!

441
00:19:06,375 --> 00:19:08,000
♪

442
00:19:08,083 --> 00:19:09,500
This has gotta be
the crustiest,

443
00:19:09,583 --> 00:19:10,958
oldest tunnel
I've ever been inside.

444
00:19:11,041 --> 00:19:12,333
Well, yeah,
you can tell it's old

445
00:19:12,416 --> 00:19:13,958
by the way it takes forever
to stand up.

446
00:19:14,041 --> 00:19:16,166
And I'm pretty sure
this shaft is hollow.

447
00:19:16,250 --> 00:19:18,125
[BOTH grunting]

448
00:19:18,208 --> 00:19:21,083
♪

449
00:19:21,166 --> 00:19:22,916
There's usually an opening
at the very top

450
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:24,208
where we can pop out.

451
00:19:24,291 --> 00:19:25,416
You think we're gonna make it?

452
00:19:25,500 --> 00:19:27,125
I don't know.
This was pretty stupid.

453
00:19:27,208 --> 00:19:29,333
You're making me nervous now.
What's going to happen to us?

454
00:19:29,416 --> 00:19:31,208
Whatever it is,
just let it happen

455
00:19:31,291 --> 00:19:32,833
and hope it's over quickly.

456
00:19:34,416 --> 00:19:36,375
[BOTH screaming]

457
00:19:38,791 --> 00:19:40,083
[ROBBY gasps]

458
00:19:40,166 --> 00:19:41,625
Bet you didn't see
that one coming.

459
00:19:41,708 --> 00:19:43,625
I'm cold and wet and I hate it!

460
00:19:43,708 --> 00:19:46,125
Well, I never ruled out
the possibility.

461
00:19:46,208 --> 00:19:48,458
Of course! You're never wrong
about anything, Hatchi!

462
00:19:48,541 --> 00:19:50,250
This could be the first time
if we're crawling

463
00:19:50,333 --> 00:19:51,958
-to our death right now!
-[ROBBY] Oh, shut up!

464
00:19:52,041 --> 00:19:56,416
♪

465
00:19:56,500 --> 00:19:57,791
[ROBBY]
Who's the man?

466
00:19:57,875 --> 00:19:58,958
-Hurry!
-[ROBBY straining]

467
00:19:59,041 --> 00:20:01,416
♪

468
00:20:23,291 --> 00:20:26,750
♪

469
00:20:26,833 --> 00:20:29,666
[ROBBY]
Oh! Man, that was close!

470
00:20:29,750 --> 00:20:31,750
[HATCHI] Can't believe
we didn't catch anything.

471
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:34,291
[ROBBY]
Bro, listen.

472
00:20:34,375 --> 00:20:36,500
Sure, money can buy you chicks
and happiness,

473
00:20:36,583 --> 00:20:37,916
and "stuff," but...

474
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:40,125
none of that matters
if you're dead, you know?

475
00:20:41,541 --> 00:20:44,041
It was a good effort.
You can't win 'em all, big guy.

476
00:20:44,125 --> 00:20:46,791
Hey, we're all still going
to Isekandar, aren't we?

477
00:20:46,875 --> 00:20:48,125
That's gonna be the cat's naps!

478
00:20:48,208 --> 00:20:49,541
I wish.

479
00:20:49,625 --> 00:20:51,625
But not if Hizakuriger's down.

480
00:20:51,708 --> 00:20:52,875
Sorry.

481
00:20:52,958 --> 00:20:55,125
Oh, no need to apologize!

482
00:20:55,208 --> 00:20:57,166
Actually, it was after
I pulled you two from the sea

483
00:20:57,250 --> 00:20:58,833
that I realized
something great about myself!

484
00:20:58,916 --> 00:21:00,791
Turns out my gills
will work just fine

485
00:21:00,875 --> 00:21:02,875
with a little more
underwater training!

486
00:21:02,958 --> 00:21:04,791
And so, I'll be
forever grateful to you!

487
00:21:04,875 --> 00:21:06,375
We should be grateful!

488
00:21:06,458 --> 00:21:09,083
There's no need to thank us
for putting you in danger.

489
00:21:09,166 --> 00:21:10,333
What now?

490
00:21:14,791 --> 00:21:17,125
-Is that...
-It's the Odwarla oarfish!

491
00:21:17,208 --> 00:21:21,125
♪

492
00:21:21,208 --> 00:21:22,666
[ALL grunt]

493
00:21:22,750 --> 00:21:25,083
♪

494
00:21:25,166 --> 00:21:27,250
[ALL panting]

495
00:21:27,333 --> 00:21:29,875
Hmm. Predictable, but whatevs.

496
00:21:29,958 --> 00:21:31,125
[camera shutter clicks]

497
00:21:32,750 --> 00:21:34,333
♪

498
00:21:34,416 --> 00:21:36,625
[IKKU] I can't tell you how
happy I am to be outta there!

499
00:21:36,708 --> 00:21:39,250
Same! But we caught
the oarfish!

500
00:21:39,333 --> 00:21:40,833
And all the reward money!

501
00:21:40,916 --> 00:21:42,416
Yeah, but we had
to use most of it

502
00:21:42,500 --> 00:21:44,250
to pay off your hot nurse
for that supreme set

503
00:21:44,333 --> 00:21:45,458
of fish sticks
or whatever it was.

504
00:21:45,541 --> 00:21:47,625
